., polypeptides that bind to the regulatory sequence and/or the nucleic acid). Examples of regulatory sequences include promoters, enhancers and other expression control elements (
e.g
., polyadenylation signals). Further examples of regulatory sequences are described in, for example, 
Goeddel, 1990, Gene Expression Technology: Methods in 
 and 
Baron et al., 1995, Nucleic Acids Res. 23:3605-06
.






