High plasma IGF-1 and reduced IGFbp3 in men 40-80 years old is associated with increased prostate cancer risk (
Chan et al., 1998, Science 279: 563-6
). High IGF-1 is associated with a risk of other cancers including breast (
Hankinson et al., 1998, Lancet 351: 1393-96
), colon (
Ma et al., 1999, Journal of the National Cancer Institute 91: 620-25
) and lung (
Yu et al., 1999, Journal of the National Cancer Institute 91: 151-56
). In transgenic mouse models, tumor incidence is increased by IGF-1 overexpression in diverse locations (
Bol et al., 1997, Oncogene 14: 1725-34
; 
DiGiovanni et al., 2000, Cancer Research 60: 1561-70
; 
DiGiovanni et al., 2000, Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America 97: 3455-60
